                </div>
                <div class="pricing-card">
                    <h3>SaaS Growth Team</h3>
                    <p class="pricing-card__price" style="font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: bold;">Ask for pricing</p>
                    <p class="pricing-card__description">Our experienced team integrates product, user experience, and user journeys into a growth-generating whole.</p>
                    <a href="/en/contact" class="btn btn--primary">Request contact &rarr;</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p class="pricing__note" style="text-align: center; margin-top: var(--spacing-lg);">*For small companies with less than five million euros in turnover, we offer our services at a reduced rate of €95/hour. Prices are tax-free (VAT 0%).</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Schedule Meeting Section -->
    <section class="schedule-meeting" id="schedule-meeting">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="section__header" style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);">
                <h2 class="section__title" style="color: #9C2043; font-weight: bold;">Book a meeting</h2>
                <p class="section__subtitle">Schedule a time and let's see how we can help your team succeed</p>
            </div>
            <div class="schedule-meeting__embed">
                <CalendlyEmbed elementId="cal-inline-index" calLink="aaltoyleva/kartoitustapaaminen" />
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section class="faq-section" id="faq">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="section__header" style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);">
                <h2 class="section__title" style="color: #9C2043; font-weight: bold;">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
                <p class="section__subtitle">Answers to the most common questions about our services</p>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-items">
                <!-- FAQ Item 1 -->
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question-wrapper">
                        <span class="faq-question">How long do I need to commit?</span>
                        <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <p class="faq-answer">Our contracts are valid until further notice, so the minimum commitment is one month. This allows for flexible collaboration and gives you the freedom to scale our services according to your needs. Typically, our clients work with us for 2-6 months depending on the scope of the project.</p>
                </div>
                <!-- FAQ Item 2 -->
                <div class="faq-item">
                     <div class="faq-question-wrapper">
                        <span class="faq-question">How do you differentiate yourselves from other design agencies?</span>
                        <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <p class="faq-answer">We specialize specifically in SaaS product design and deeply understand the industry's unique characteristics. We combine product strategy, UI design, and marketing into one cohesive whole. We have strong experience in conversion optimization and user journey design, especially in the SaaS context.</p>
                </div>
                <!-- FAQ Item 3 -->
                 <div class="faq-item">
                     <div class="faq-question-wrapper">
                        <span class="faq-question">What tools do you use for design?</span>
                        <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <p class="faq-answer">We use modern design tools like Figma for UI/UX design, Miro for user journey mapping and workshop facilitation, and Hotjar for user analytics. We also leverage AI-based tools in user research and data analytics to ensure a data-driven design process.</p>
                </div>
                <!-- FAQ Item 4 -->
                <div class="faq-item">
                     <div class="faq-question-wrapper">
                        <span class="faq-question">How do you ensure that design supports our business goals?</span>
                        <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <p class="faq-answer">We always start by mapping your business goals and metrics. We conduct a thorough positioning exercise that helps understand your target audience and competitive advantage. Our design process is based on continuous measurement and optimization to ensure the design's effectiveness on conversion and growth.</p>
                </div>
                <!-- FAQ Item 5 -->
                 <div class="faq-item">
                     <div class="faq-question-wrapper">
                        <span class="faq-question">Can you help with developing an existing product?</span>
                        <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <p class="faq-answer">Yes, we help with both designing new products and developing existing ones. We first conduct a thorough analysis of your current product, gather user data, and identify development areas. Based on this, we create a development plan that can be implemented in phases without disrupting existing business.</p>
                </div>
                <!-- FAQ Item 6 -->
                 <div class="faq-item">
                     <div class="faq-question-wrapper">
                        <span class="faq-question">How do you handle complex SaaS products?</span>
                        <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <p class="faq-answer">We have strong experience in designing complex B2B SaaS products. We use proven methods and frameworks that help transform even a complex system into a clear user interface. Our outside perspective often helps see simplification opportunities that an internal team might not notice.</p>
                </div>
                <!-- FAQ Item 7 -->
                 <div class="faq-item">
                     <div class="faq-question-wrapper">
                        <span class="faq-question">How do you ensure designer availability for our project?</span>
                        <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <p class="faq-answer">We don't oversell our resources, but always ensure our designers have enough time to focus on your project. Typically, one designer works on 2-3 projects simultaneously, enabling both efficient work and sufficient flexibility in urgent situations.</p>
                </div>
                <!-- FAQ Item 8 -->
                 <div class="faq-item">
                     <div class="faq-question-wrapper">
                        <span class="faq-question">What if I'm not satisfied with the result?</span>
                        <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <p class="faq-answer">Our work comes with a full satisfaction guarantee. If you're not happy with our work, you don't pay anything. We work iteratively and collect feedback regularly to ensure we're on the right track. This approach minimizes the risk that the final result wouldn't meet your expectations.</p>
                </div>
                <!-- FAQ Item 9 -->
                 <div class="faq-item">
                     <div class="faq-question-wrapper">
                        <span class="faq-question">How do you support the development team in implementation?</span>
                        <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <p class="faq-answer">We always provide precise technical specifications and style guides to the development team. We use Figma's developer view and create a component library if needed. We're also available for consultation during implementation and help solve any technical challenges in design implementation.</p>
                </div>
                <!-- FAQ Item 10 -->
                 <div class="faq-item">
                     <div class="faq-question-wrapper">
                        <span class="faq-question">How do you price larger projects?</span>
                        <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <p class="faq-answer">For larger projects, we can agree on a fixed monthly budget or project-specific pricing. Our hourly rate is €110/hour (€95/hour for smaller companies), but we always customize pricing according to the project scope and needs. We create a clear project plan defining the necessary resources and timeline.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Blog Preview Section -->
    <section class="blog-preview" id="latest-posts">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="section__header" style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);">
                <h2 class="section__title">Our latest thoughts</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="blog-grid">
                {latestPosts.map(post => (
                    <article class="blog-card">
                        <a href={`/en/blog/${post.slug}/`} class="blog-card__link">
                            {post.data.heroImage && (
                               <div class="blog-card__image-container">
                                 <Image
                                   src={post.data.heroImage}
                                   alt={post.data.heroImageAlt || post.data.title}
                                   width={800}
                                   height={450}
                                   format="webp"
                                   quality={80}
                                   loading="lazy"
                                   decoding="async"
                                   class="blog-card__image"
                                 />
                               </div>
                            )}
                            <div class="blog-card__content">
                                 {post.data.tags && post.data.tags.length > 0 && (
                                    <div class="blog-card__tags">
                                        {post.data.tags.map(tag => (
                                            <span class="tag">{tag}</span>
                                        ))}
                                    </div>
                                 )}
                                <h3 class="blog-card__title">{post.data.title}</h3>
                                <p class="blog-card__excerpt">{post.data.description || 'Read article...'}</p>
                                <div class="blog-card__footer">
                                    <span class="blog-card__readmore">Read more &rarr;</span>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </a>
                    </article>
                ))}
            </div>
            <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: var(--spacing-lg);">
                <a href="/en/blog" class="btn btn--secondary">Read all articles &rarr;</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
    .team-grid {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column; /* Stack vertically by default (mobile) */
        align-items: center; /* Center items horizontally in column layout */
        gap: var(--spacing-lg);
    }

    .team-member {
        text-align: center; /* Ensure text inside member card is centered */
    }

    /* Apply row layout for medium screens and up */
    @media (min-width: 768px) {
        .team-grid {
            flex-direction: row; /* Arrange side-by-side */
            justify-content: center; /* Center items horizontally in row layout */
        }
    }
</style>
